content:
This game is in all ways perfect, the story is so good, just as good, if 
not better than I've heard from others. Didn't want to put it down through 
the entire story. The pixel art is gorgeous. Characters are great, music is 
really good. Even though its repeated a lot, I can keep listening to it. 
Together with Icey and muse dash, this game is in my top games I've played 
ever.

It's good. It's so good. The gameplay itself was simple, consisting of a 
few story-related choices, puzzles and search games that may get repetitive 
by the end. If you're sticking around for a pure game, this isn't a good 
install for you. HOWEVER. If you don't care about that aspect and would 
like to stick around for a story, please play this game. It invokes many 
deep emotions throughout. The characters are all wonderful (especially Dr. 
Watts!) and you get truly sucked into what they do. I won't spoil anything, 
but it had me a little teary-eyed at the end.

A very emotional and well balanced game, including tactic, strategy, and 
even a little bit of fighting.

Falls apart at the 5th chapter. Don't understand why everyone thinks it's 
so great. I think the dialogue was well written between the main 
characters, but the story falls apart with a cheap ending. Controls are 
pretty awful. I don't understand the moral of the story, kind of a rip off 
of Eternal Sunshine of The Spotless Mind..which had a point.. I think the 
real relationship with his wife was way better the artificial one they 
cobbled together..so what's the moral? A fake reality is better then life? 
Also the two main doctors seem barely changed by the emotional outcome, 
another day in the office? All in all I felt let down, seems like a game 
for the casual phone "gamer"..I do say tho River was an excellent character 
that tugs at your heart

*Best emotional coaster on 8-bit* I have never written a review for a game 
in my life, and I never thought i would, but here i am. This game, changed 
my view of the world and life. If i were ever given a chance to wipe my 
memory so that i could experience all the emotions playing this game the 
first time gave me, i would do it in a heartbeat. Please release a bird 
story and finding paradise on mobile, the mobile interface seems like a 
much more suitable platform for 8 bit games nowadays. Anyway, thank you for 
this slice of wholesome art that you've shared with us, and i hope to see 
more from you freebird games!

Music - 5/5 i loved the music. The whole soundtrack combined with the wonderful visuals, complemented the beautiful story. The gameplay wasn't very engaging - just wandering around triggering cutscenes and finding five items per level. To get to the next level, you can solve a small puzzle, but nothing super challenging. There's no element of choice, so it's basically just an interactive story. And the story itself is... Lackluster. The two main doctor characters are unlikeable stereotypes (an uptight woman and a "laid-back" man who doesn't respect boundaries). The POV character doesn't have a personality except that he loves this one woman/girl, River. And River is supposed to be autistic but she doesn't read like autistic people I've known. She's sweet but they treat her like a freak, both her lover and one of the doctors, so that throws me off a lot. Idk, it just... Didn't have much to offer.

content: The most emotionally touching and beautiful story a video game has ever told. Better than 90% of any romantic comedy or drama movie or book ever released.  Enter a dying old man's mind to alter his memories so he can die believing he went to the moon. Learn every one of his reasons for wanting to go "To The Moon." I don't care how stoic you are, you will cry tears of joy.  The ending is worth $40. For $2, it would be a crime not to buy it and experience this wonderful story. Remember Pixar's Up? That early montage of the old man's life? This is like that cranked up to 10.

Absolutely my favorite game when I discovered it on PC.  Now that it is on mobile, I can carry it with me anywhere.  Amazing heartfelt story that will truly bring tears to your eyes.  Also the most amazing video game soundtrack I have ever heard with "Everything's Alright" simultaneously bringing a tear to my eye and making me feel better about life at the same time.  Plus the way it features not one, but two autistic characters (and female ones at that!) in an incredibly realistic and relatable way was very moving, especially as someone on the spectrum.  I actually have a screenshot (from the PC version) of a quote from one of the autistic characters as my Facebook banner.  5/5... Top scores all around!
